8... Qf6 9. Ne2
{ With Bc3 to come and once again a typical compensation. Note that the engines very often give 0.00 in these positions, but it only confirms, that White has full compensation for the b-pawn. In practice handling Black's position is extremely difficult and I would expect to see many mistakes here. }
